703577f-b.text:
109-111 Clark Street, between Henry and Fulton Streets. (In the foreground, is seen Monroe Place, a short street beginning at Clark Street,
and running west to the East River).
April 13, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
(u)
The same, showing the same view nine years earlier.
1922.
Augene L. Armbruster Collection.

704829f-b.text:
Henry Street, west side, south of Clark Street, showing the First Presbyterian Church. This edifice, the congregation's
second, was erected in 1846.
Views 1,AI  Eugene L. Armbruster Collection View 1: 1922
MAY BE REPRODUCED  View,3: 1923
View 2 P. L. Sperr  Ve. MS April 4, 1932

704830f-b.text:
Henry Street, west side, at Clark Street, viewing north across the latter. At the S.W. corner is the First Methodist Episcopal Church and across the street is the Hotel St. George.
View 2 also shows a portion of the First Presbyterian Church (left).
View 1: March 1, 1929
View 2: April 4, 1932

P.L. Sperr
